    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Let's stick to 120. The upcoming style guide has not changed.\r\n> \r\n> I do not support changing the value to 100, despite personally using it.\r\n> \r\n> Of course if you do statistical analysis, the mean is 100.\r\n\r\njust to let you know, this isn't a LOC count value [^1]; you can have over 120 characters and still not trigger the formatter if, for example, the function uses really long words, etc. So the original solidity issue is incorrect in its conclusion as its motivation statement referenced directly LOC w.r.t monitor sizes.\r\n\r\n[reference comment in issue](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/pull/12681#issue-1139515157)\r\n\r\nEdit: 120 is cool too. At the end of the day I would advocate for a larger value like 120 as it helps reduce diff churn vs a lower bound value. \r\n\r\n[^1]: this is how prettier works and all other pretty-print formatters that I know of, YMMV however. ",
